Diagnosis. Adult (
Fig. 8
) with wingspan 20.0 – 30.5 mm . This species is characterized by the sella ventrally directed and apically far exceeding the ventral margin of the valva in the male genitalia (
Fig. 17
), and the narrow antrum with setae on the straight posterior margin, and the horn-shaped membranous sacs from between the antrum and the ductus bursae curved backward in the female genitalia (
Fig. 24
).
